sourcesContent:
const TweetInfo = [
    {
        id: "@EdouardMendy",
        name: "Edouard Mendy",
        pp: "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1311248843439251456/LmWEVVet_400x400.jpg",
        tweet:"Man does not weave this web of life. He is merely a strand of it. Whatever he does to the web, he does to himself.",
        time:"10h"
    },
    {
        id: "@thiagosilva",
        name: "Thiago Silva",
        pp: "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1299361522787864582/5CAtSZzI_400x400.jpg",
        tweet:"dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum",
        time:"10h"
    },
    {
        id: "@Zouma5",
        name: "Kurt Zouma",
        pp: "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1313047449657913344/2dErpfsV_400x400.jpg",
        tweet:"O, what a tangled web we weave when first we practise to deceive!",
        time:"10h"
    },
    {
        id: "@chilly3",
        name: "Ben Chilwell",
        pp: "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1189684118289887246/TvbH7rsE_400x400.jpg",
        tweet:"Laws are spider webs through which the big flies pass and the little ones get caught.",
        time:"10h"
    },
    {
        id: "@rjames",
        name: "Reece James",
        pp: "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1344707747284201473/QpnI6RZ4_400x400.jpg",
        tweet:"A true community is not just about being geographically close to someone or part of the same social web network. It's about feeling connected and responsible for what happens. Humanity is our ultimate community, and everyone plays a crucial role.",
        time:"10h"
    },
    {
        id: "@ngkante13",
        name: "Ngolo Kante",
        pp: "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1018823690459508736/2yyZrszu_400x400.jpg",
        tweet:"Written laws are like spiders' webs, and will, like them, only entangle and hold the poor and weak, while the rich and powerful will easily break through them",
        time:"10h"
    },
    {
        id: "@masonmount10",
        name: "Mason Mount",
        pp: "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1327047201214914562/IhkM21jy_400x400.jpg",
        tweet:"I'm OK with procedural code, and the web is a top-down type of problem. It makes sense to me that you have HTML, you spit out a bunch of HTML, then you call a function to do something and then call another function.",
        time:"10h"
    },
    {
        id: "@mkocavic",
        name: "Mateo Kovacic",
        pp: "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1269395572441722887/EZakN5bD_400x400.jpg",
        tweet:"Talking, talking. Spinning a web of words, pale walls of dreams, between myself and all I see.",
        time:"10h"
    },
    {
        id: "@HZ22",
        name: "Hakim Ziyech",
        pp: "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1329147701787815940/7gCshclx_400x400.jpg",
        tweet:"When something is such a creative medium as the web, the limits to it are our imagination.",
        time:"10h"
    },
    {
        id: "@puli10",
        name: "Christian Pulisic",
        pp: "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1339380345041539074/chrpX5SN_400x400.jpg",
        tweet:"It's very, very difficult to reinvent yourself when you're 40 or 50, whether you are a taxi driver who now needs to become a web designer, or anything else. It just becomes more difficult and more scary.",
        time:"10h"
    },
    {
        id: "@timowerner11",
        name: "Timo Werner",
        pp: "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1288962100728078343/dyn6bTq4_400x400.jpg",
        tweet:"The important thing is the diversity available on the Web.",
        time:"10h"
    }
]

export default TweetInfo
